<subSubSection id="9B64850388108B6D77A51F6B1301076C" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="notes">
<paragraph id="2FFB17A486853D8C7D87B6E9744B7FC0" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A14FEFF936C628A2E1F47D4C297C1701" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
This species produces non-ostiolate ascomata and citriform, smooth-walled ascospores. Other species previously placed in 
<taxonomicName id="797EF6BF77AA85373F237F3470CD3957" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Melanospora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanospora" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanospora</taxonomicName>
characterized by the production of non-ostiolate ascomata and smooth-walled ascospores are 
<taxonomicName id="10F0E1CFC4128D22D2FD08A9FFC17B74" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. hypomyces" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="hypomyces">Mi. hypomyces</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5D9499ADAE9B95C2782C0FB84AB414EE" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. levitum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="levitum">Mi. levitum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C1741DF13E1BA9FA3A4D9C83BACD03F7" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. zobelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="zobelii">Mi. zobelii</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="C5584886BF9EEAC1D311B87EA1E5CE93" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium hypomyces" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="hypomyces">Microthecium hypomyces</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by its fusiform ascospores (citriform in the other species), and 
<taxonomicName id="A0719576D37B351FE4A1840376D38CA4" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. levitum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="levitum">Mi. levitum</taxonomicName>
by the presence of bulbils and a phialidic asexual morph. 
<taxonomicName id="E8E91347E3500FCAC46E56260B7FCDD7" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium geoporae" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="geoporae">Microthecium geoporae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="14228C392EE40ADFD82ADBD7C468A027" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. zobelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="zobelii">Mi. zobelii</taxonomicName>
are distinguished by the size of their ascospores [28-30 
<normalizedToken id="B1D3BD1B5355218456F729AF6A399943" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
12
<normalizedToken id="DD7EBE96B0CD529648909D11654076E8" originalValue="–13(–">-13(-</normalizedToken>
15) 
<normalizedToken id="C372389341D9AC571A5A839F7ECED57B" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="85AA3F491F0958AC24046D5D609D5DF7" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. geoporae" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="geoporae">Mi. geoporae</taxonomicName>
and 18-25 
<normalizedToken id="6776275887BADB67B7C04DF3F8ABD296" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
8.5-12 
<normalizedToken id="31AD82CCD08FA193002735DC2EC66106" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-9 
<normalizedToken id="12C46E29DE70B4D881C54A24065CF5C2" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName id="2BE8C019CD6BA68AE9081121212E2ABE" genus="Mi." lsidName="Mi. zobelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="zobelii">Mi. zobelii</taxonomicName>
]. 
<taxonomicName id="E97AD49BF04F7CD672BEE2D05F0E4545" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ceratostomataceae" genus="Microthecium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Microthecium tenuissimum" order="Melanosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tenuissimum">Microthecium tenuissimum</taxonomicName>
shows similar morphological features to these species but its ascospores are finely reticulate under SEM and its ascomata are smaller (less than 120 
<normalizedToken id="8E145C21DE744B6DEF857190CA03B3D9" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
) than in the other species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
